# ARQIVE — Cursor Rules File (v2)
## AI-Powered Audit Intelligence Platform
### Complete context: architecture · decisions · prototype · product vision

---

## HOW TO USE THIS FILE

Save the entire file as `.cursorrules` in the root of your project.
Cursor reads it automatically for every session.

When starting a new session, open with:
  "Build [module name] following .cursorrules exactly."

Never ask Cursor to deviate from the stack, versions, or rules here.
If Cursor suggests something different, reject it and refer back to this file.

---

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 1 — WHAT ARQIVE IS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## Product identity

ARQIVE is an on-premise AI-powered audit document intelligence platform.

It is sold as a **licensed software package** installed on the buying
company's own server. Employees use it through a standard web browser.
No document data, query text, or inference ever leaves the company's
own infrastructure. Zero cloud API calls at runtime. Zero per-query cost.

## The problem it solves

Auditors work with large sets of PDFs, Word files, and spreadsheets.
Plain keyword search is not enough. They need:
  - Semantic search (meaning-based, not keyword)
  - Structured filters (date, amount, category, document type, count)
  - Answers that cite their source (which document, which page)
  - A confidence signal so they know when to verify manually
  - Role-based access control — not everyone should see everything
  - An immutable audit trail for compliance and regulatory purposes

## Business model (important — shapes every technical decision)

- We (the ARQIVE team) sell an **annual software license** per client
- We install the software on the **client's own server** remotely
- Employees get a browser URL — **nothing to install on their machines**
- Ongoing cost to the client: ~£10–18/month electricity only
- No cloud bills, no per-query charges, no third-party AI costs ever
- Revenue: license fee + optional support contract per client
- Each client = one fully isolated deployment, no shared infrastructure

## Competitive positioning

Most AI audit tools are cloud-based, charge per user per month,
and require audit data to leave the company. ARQIVE does the opposite:
fixed annual license, runs on their hardware, fully air-gapped.
For regulated industries (banking, insurance, healthcare, government)
this is often the ONLY model that passes procurement.

## Current stage

We are building the prototype/demo version first.
The prototype must work as a proper product — not a toy.
Real documents, real RBAC, real citations, real audit log.
The only difference from production is it runs locally or on a
free Oracle Cloud VM rather than on a client's dedicated server.

