# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 3 — TECH STACK DECISIONS (FINAL — DO NOT CHANGE)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## LLM
- Model: llama3.2:3b (Q4_K_M quantisation)
- Runtime: Ollama (local, no internet after model pull)
- Why chosen: best balance of accuracy/RAM/speed at 3B params for
  audit document Q&A. Tested against Phi-3 Mini and Gemma 2 2B.
  Llama 3.2 3B wins on multi-document synthesis and numerical reasoning.
- temperature=0.1 (near-deterministic — audit accuracy requires this)
- top_p=0.9, repeat_penalty=1.1, num_ctx=4096, num_predict=512
- Binding: HARDCODED to http://127.0.0.1:11434 (not from env)

## Embeddings
- Model: sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2
- Device: cpu (ALWAYS — never cuda, system must work CPU-only)
- RAM: ~400 MB, loads at app startup as singleton
- Output: 384-dimensional normalised float vectors
- Batch size: 32 for ingestion, 1 for query-time

## Vector store
- ChromaDB 0.5.0 (PersistentClient — NOT the old Client() API)
- One collection per tenant: "arqive_{tenant_id}"
- Always filter by tenant_id in every ChromaDB query

## Metadata + relational DB
- Dev: SQLite via aiosqlite (async)
- Prod: PostgreSQL 16 via asyncpg (async)
- ORM: SQLAlchemy 2.0 declarative style with type annotations
- Migrations: Alembic (manual in prod — never autogenerate in prod)

## API framework
- FastAPI 0.111.0 with Uvicorn
- SSE (Server-Sent Events) for streaming LLM responses
- JWT auth via python-jose, passwords via passlib/bcrypt
- Rate limiting via slowapi: 60 req/min per user on query endpoints

## Task queue
- Celery 5.4.0 with Redis 7.2 as broker
- All document ingestion runs as Celery background tasks
- Never run ingestion inline in a FastAPI request handler

## Document parsing
- PDF: pdfplumber 0.11.0 (do NOT install pdfminer.six separately)
- Word: python-docx 1.1.2
- Excel/CSV: openpyxl 3.1.2

## Frontend
- React 18.3.1 + TypeScript 5.4.5
- Build: Vite 5.2.12
- State: Zustand 4.5.2
- Data fetching: TanStack Query 5.40.0
- Styling: Tailwind CSS 3.4.4 (no UI component library — plain Tailwind)
- No lodash, no date libraries (use native JS Intl)
- SSE consumer for streaming query responses

## Infrastructure
- Reverse proxy: Nginx (SSL termination, SSE buffering disabled)
- Containerisation: Docker + Docker Compose
- Dev: docker-compose.yml (SQLite, hot reload)
- Prod: docker-compose.prod.yml (PostgreSQL, nginx, restart:always)

## Document storage (company's own — ARQIVE only reads)
- Local filesystem (dev/demo)
- AWS S3 (company's own bucket — NOT a third-party service)
- MinIO (self-hosted S3-compatible, for companies without AWS)
- ARQIVE connects read-only. Documents never copied to ARQIVE node.
- boto3 works for both S3 and MinIO (same API, different endpoint URL)

