# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 6 — DATABASE SCHEMA
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

All models use SQLAlchemy 2.0 declarative style with Mapped[] annotations.
All PKs are UUID. All timestamps are UTC. Use timezone-aware datetimes.

## tenants
```python
id: UUID PK
name: str                   # company display name
slug: str UNIQUE            # url-safe, e.g. "acme-corp"
license_key: str            # bcrypt-hashed
license_expires_at: datetime
is_active: bool DEFAULT True
max_users: int DEFAULT 10
created_at: datetime
updated_at: datetime
```

## users
```python
id: UUID PK
tenant_id: UUID FK→tenants  # UNIQUE constraint: (email, tenant_id)
email: str
hashed_password: str NULL   # null for SSO-only users
full_name: str
role: Enum["viewer","auditor","admin"]
is_active: bool DEFAULT True
last_login_at: datetime NULL
created_at: datetime
```

## documents
```python
id: UUID PK
tenant_id: UUID FK→tenants
uploaded_by: UUID FK→users
filename: str
source_path: str            # S3/MinIO/local path — never a copy
file_type: Enum["pdf","docx","xlsx","csv"]
file_size_bytes: int
page_count: int NULL
doc_date: date NULL         # extracted or user-supplied
category: str NULL          # "invoice","audit_report","contract" etc
status: Enum["pending","indexed","failed"]
chunk_count: int DEFAULT 0
# ARRAY stored as JSON for SQLite compat, native ARRAY in PostgreSQL
allowed_roles: JSON         # ["viewer","auditor","admin"]
allowed_user_ids: JSON      # [] means role-only, no user overrides
metadata_json: JSON NULL    # arbitrary extracted metadata
created_at: datetime
updated_at: datetime
```

## chunks
```python
id: UUID PK                 # SAME UUID used in ChromaDB — enables joins
document_id: UUID FK→documents
tenant_id: UUID             # denormalised — avoids join on every retrieval
chunk_index: int
page_number: int
text_preview: str(200)      # first 200 chars — for UI display only
token_count: int
embedding_model: str        # "all-MiniLM-L6-v2"
created_at: datetime
```

## audit_log — APPEND ONLY, NO UPDATE OR DELETE
```python
id: UUID PK
tenant_id: UUID
user_id: UUID
action: Enum["query","upload","delete","login","logout","admin_action"]
timestamp: datetime         # server UTC — never client-supplied
query_text: str NULL        # queries only
document_ids_accessed: JSON # list of UUIDs
chunk_ids_accessed: JSON    # list of UUIDs
prompt_hash: str NULL       # SHA-256 of full prompt (queries only)
response_hash: str NULL     # SHA-256 of LLM response (queries only)
confidence_score: float NULL
latency_ms: int NULL
ip_address: str NULL
row_hash: str               # SHA-256(all fields) tamper detection
# DB enforcement:
# REVOKE UPDATE, DELETE ON audit_log FROM arqive_app_user;
```

