# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 13 — PROTOTYPE / DEMO SETUP
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

The prototype IS the product. It uses the full production stack.
The only difference is the hosting environment.

## Three environments to support

### Environment 1: Local (your Windows machine)
- Use docker-compose.yml
- Start with: make dev && make pull-model && make init-db
- Access: http://localhost:3000
- Share via ngrok: ngrok http 3000
- RAM needed: ~6 GB (close Chrome tabs before demoing on 8 GB)

### Environment 2: Oracle Cloud Free VM (always-on demo)
- 4 ARM CPUs + 24 GB RAM — permanently free
- Use docker-compose.demo.yml
- All images are ARM-compatible (Ollama has native ARM support)
- Get free static IP from Oracle — never changes
- Add free SSL via Let's Encrypt: certbot --nginx -d your.domain.com
- Share via permanent URL — no laptop required

### Environment 3: Client's own server (production)
- Use docker-compose.prod.yml
- PostgreSQL replaces SQLite
- Nginx with SSL termination
- Clients access via their internal LAN URL

## Demo seed script (scripts/seed_demo.py)

This script must:
1. Create three demo users:
   - viewer@demo.arqive.com   / DemoViewer123!
   - auditor@demo.arqive.com  / DemoAuditor123!
   - admin@demo.arqive.com    / DemoAdmin123!
2. Create a demo tenant: "ARQIVE Demo Organisation"
3. Load 3–5 sample audit PDFs from data/demo_docs/ into the index
4. Run 3 warm-up queries to pre-load the LLM context
5. Print a summary of what was seeded

## Demo documents to use (free, publicly available)
- UK National Audit Office reports: nao.org.uk (search "value for money")
- UK company annual reports: Companies House
- Local council audit reports: any UK council website
Store in data/demo_docs/ — commit small ones (<5 MB) to the repo.

## Five demo queries (pre-run these before every client demo)

1. "What were the top audit findings across all documents?"
   → Shows: multi-document synthesis, ranking

2. "What is the total value of contracts flagged for concern?"
   → Shows: numerical extraction, structured data handling

3. "What recommendations were made regarding procurement controls?"
   → Shows: precise citations with page numbers

4. "What was the auditor's name in 2019?" (if not in docs)
   → Shows: honest gap detection — says "not in documents" not hallucination

5. Run the same query twice — show audit log shows both entries
   → Shows: immutable compliance trail

## 10-minute demo script
- Min 0–2:  Log in as auditor. Show document list with real report names.
- Min 2–4:  Run Query 1. Watch streaming. Click a citation to show source.
- Min 4–6:  Run Query 4 (gap detection). "It doesn't make things up."
- Min 6–8:  Switch to admin. Open audit log. Show query logged with hash.
- Min 8–10: Switch to viewer. Try to upload (blocked). Show RBAC live.

---

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 14 — DEPLOYMENT AND HOSTING
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## Hosting strategy (in order of use)

### Development
- Your Windows machine with Docker Desktop
- Ollama installed natively on Windows (not in Docker)
  → Set OLLAMA_HOST=127.0.0.1 in Windows system env vars

### Demo / sharing
- Option A (instant): ngrok http 3000 — tunnels localhost to public URL
  Free tier: random URL each session
  Paid (£8/mo): fixed subdomain e.g. demo.arqive.ngrok.app
- Option B (permanent free): Cloudflare Tunnel (cloudflared)
  Requires: free Cloudflare account + any domain
  Fixed URL forever, completely free
- Option C (always-on): Oracle Cloud Always Free ARM VM
  24 GB RAM, 4 CPUs, 200 GB disk — permanently free
  ARM-native Docker images work with no code changes

### Production (client deployments)
- Primary: client's own server — on-premise or their private cloud
  Minimum spec: 16 GB RAM, modern CPU, 500 GB SSD
  Recommended: 32 GB RAM + RTX 3060 GPU (drops response 15s → 2s)
- Secondary (client has no server): Hetzner Cloud
  CX42: 8 vCPU, 16 GB RAM → ~£14/month — far cheaper than AWS/Azure
  EU data centres — GDPR-friendly for audit market

### Frontend hosting (any environment)
- Dev: Vite dev server on localhost:3000
- Demo/Prod: Served by Nginx in the Docker stack — no separate hosting
- Optional: Vercel or Cloudflare Pages for CDN-hosted static build
  (only if decoupling frontend from backend server)

## Platform decisions (final)
- DO NOT use: Vercel, Netlify, Render, Railway (serverless — Ollama incompatible)
- DO NOT use: Heroku, Fly.io free tier (512 MB RAM — far too small)
- DO NOT use: Hugging Face Spaces (no persistent volumes, sleeps)
- USE for demo: Oracle Cloud Free Tier (24 GB ARM VM)
- USE for prod: client's own server or Hetzner VPS

