# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 15 — PRODUCT VISION AND ROADMAP
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## What we are building toward

ARQIVE is not just a search tool. The long-term vision is a complete
AI-native audit intelligence platform — the system auditors use
throughout their entire workflow, not just for document lookup.

## Phase 1 — Prototype (now building)
Goal: working product that can demo to first clients
- Full document ingestion pipeline (PDF, Word, Excel)
- Semantic + structured hybrid search
- RAG pipeline with citations and confidence scores
- RBAC with three roles + document-level ACL
- Immutable audit log
- SSE streaming UI
- Local and Oracle Cloud demo deployment

## Phase 2 — First clients (after prototype validation)
Goal: deploy to 2–3 paying clients, learn real usage patterns
- PostgreSQL in production
- SSO integration (Azure AD / Okta / Google Workspace)
- Client-specific document category taxonomies
- Query history and favourites per user
- Admin analytics dashboard (query volume, top documents, user activity)
- Automated document ingestion watcher (poll S3/MinIO for new files)
- License key enforcement (startup check, read-only on expiry)
- Update delivery mechanism (signed Docker image releases)

## Phase 3 — Product hardening
Goal: reliable, maintainable, scalable to 10+ clients
- Multi-model support (swap Llama 3.2 for larger model on GPU servers)
- Document annotation and comments (auditors can tag findings)
- Export query results as PDF/Word reports
- Scheduled query reports (email digest of daily findings)
- Webhook support (notify external systems on ingestion complete)
- Client-facing health dashboard
- Automated backup verification

## Phase 4 — Platform expansion
Goal: become the standard for on-premise audit AI
- Custom fine-tuning on client's own document corpus
- Multi-language document support (EU audit market)
- Integration with audit management platforms (TeamMate, CaseWare)
- Findings tracking (link query results to formal audit findings)
- Risk register integration
- Mobile-optimised read-only view

## Revenue model
- Annual software license (per client, per tier)
  Entry: up to 20 users, CPU server — target £4,000–8,000/year
  Standard: up to 100 users, GPU server — target £12,000–20,000/year
  Enterprise: 100+ users, dedicated LLM node — target £30,000+/year
- Professional services: installation and onboarding — £500–1,500 one-time
- Support contract: optional, 15–20% of license fee annually
- No per-query charges. No user-seat charges. Fixed and predictable.

## Target markets (in priority order)
1. UK accounting and audit firms (Big 4 regional offices, mid-tier firms)
2. UK public sector internal audit teams
3. UK financial services compliance teams
4. EU audit firms (after multi-language support)

## Key differentiators to always lead with
1. Data never leaves your building — passes procurement every time
2. No ongoing cloud bills — total cost of ownership is dramatically lower
3. Works offline — audit fieldwork often happens in locations without internet
4. Immutable audit trail built in — compliance teams love this
5. Cited answers with confidence scores — not a black box

