# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 16 — BUILD ORDER
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Build in this exact sequence. Each module depends on the previous.
Do not skip ahead — the foundation modules are not optional.

```
Session 1:  DB models (all 5) + Alembic initial migration
Session 2:  config.py + scripts/init_db.py + scripts/seed_demo.py
Session 3:  core/security.py (JWT + bcrypt) + core/rbac.py
Session 4:  api/auth.py (login, refresh, logout, me) + tests/test_auth.py
Session 5:  services/storage/connector.py (local/S3/MinIO abstraction)
Session 6:  services/ingestion/ (parser → chunker → embedder → indexer)
            Test on 3 real PDFs before proceeding
Session 7:  api/documents.py (upload endpoint + Celery task trigger)
Session 8:  services/retrieval/ (semantic + structured + reranker)
            Unit test each independently
Session 9:  services/retrieval/prompt.py (builder + sanitiser)
            Test with adversarial inputs before connecting LLM
Session 10: services/llm/ (client + streamer + confidence + queue)
Session 11: api/query.py (/api/query + /api/query/stream)
            End-to-end test: upload PDF → query → see citation
Session 12: frontend/src/ (SearchBar + AnswerStream + CitationCard)
            Connect to /api/query/stream SSE endpoint
Session 13: api/admin.py + frontend admin panel (users + audit log)
Session 14: docker-compose.demo.yml + nginx SSE config
Session 15: scripts/seed_demo.py + full demo run-through
Session 16: tests/ full suite (auth, rbac, ingestion, query, audit_log)
```

---

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 17 — COMMON MISTAKES TO AVOID
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## Python / backend
- NEVER use SentenceTransformer(..., device="cuda") — CPU only
- NEVER import torch at top level — import inside embedder function only
- NEVER use chromadb.Client() — use chromadb.PersistentClient(path=...)
- NEVER use asyncio.run() inside FastAPI route handlers
- NEVER use session.execute(text("SELECT ...")) — use ORM
- NEVER store JWT in localStorage — httpOnly cookie only
- NEVER log prompt content at INFO level — DEBUG only, off in prod
- NEVER use * in CORS origins — always use FRONTEND_URL env var
- NEVER run Alembic autogenerate in prod — write migrations manually
- NEVER call Ollama from frontend — always via backend API
- NEVER use numpy 2.x — pin to numpy==1.26.4 (breaks sentence-transformers)
- NEVER install pdfminer.six separately — pdfplumber brings the right version

## Docker / infrastructure
- NEVER expose Ollama on 0.0.0.0 — always 127.0.0.1:11434
- NEVER expose Redis or PostgreSQL ports publicly — internal network only
- NEVER use network_mode: host except for the ollama service
- NEVER use proxy_buffering on in nginx for SSE endpoints
- ALWAYS set restart: always on all services in demo and prod compose files

## ChromaDB 0.5.0 specific
- Client() API was removed in 0.5 — always use PersistentClient(path=...)
- EphemeralClient() for tests only
- Collection names must be lowercase alphanumeric + underscores only

## PyTorch
- The default `pip install torch` downloads a 2 GB CUDA build
- Always install with: pip install torch==2.3.0 --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu

## ARM (Oracle Cloud VM)
- All images must support linux/arm64
- ollama/ollama:latest is ARM-native — no changes needed
- All Python packages are ARM-compatible via pip
- Redis 7.2-alpine and Postgres 16-alpine both have ARM variants
- Vite/Node builds work identically on ARM

